OOP : Object Oriented Programming


1> Objects
2> Classes
3> Inheritence
4> Polymorphism
5> Abstraction
6> Encapsulation




Objects : Which exist physically and has state and behaviour  . Eg. Chair, pen , paper

Dog is an object because it has states like colour, name, breed and behaviours like tail, barking,
eating

Object is an instance of class. which contains address and takes up some memory



Class : Collection of objects , which doesnot exist physically , but a logical entity

Dog is an object whereas animal is a class
Model name is an object and car is a class


Class contains :

1> Method / function
2> Variables  : local/global
3> Constructors
4> Block : static and instance
5> Nested class and interface